statistics.name: assists
statistics.description: The number of times a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a way that leads to a score by field goal, meaning that he or she was "assisting" in the basket. There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer should be credited with an assist.

statistics.name: turnovers
statistics.description: The number of times a player loses possession to the other team.

statistics.name: minutes
statistics.description: The total number of minutes played.

statistics.name: assistTurnoverRatio
statistics.description: The average number of assists a player or team records per turnover

statistics.name: rebounds
statistics.description: The total number of rebounds (offensive and defensive).

statistics.name: defensiveRebounds
statistics.description: The number of times when the defense obtains the possession of the ball after a missed shot by the offense.

article.headline: Radford 99, Roanoke 67
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- Art Parakhouski scored 25 points and Lazar Trifunovic added 22 to lead Radford to a 99-67 victory over Roanoke on Sunday. Parakhouski, who entered as the top rebounder in Division I with 14.6 a game, also had 18 rebounds, giving him double-doubles in all eight games this season. Trifunovic, who transferred from Binghamton, also had a double-double, grabbing 11 rebounds in addition to going 10-for-14 from the floor. Radford (5-3) took a 51-27 halftime lead behind Trifunovic and Parakhouski, who combined for 30 of the Highlanders' 51 first-half points. Radford shot 58.8 percent (20-for-34) in the first half and 50.7 percent (38-for-75) for the game. The Highlanders also outrebounded the Maroons 55-29. Joey Lynch-Flohr added 18 points and Amir Johnson had 11 for Radford. Melvin Felix and Matt Crizer scored 11 each for the Roanoke (4-3), a Division III program.
